  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your<strong> aubergine[s]</strong> and discard, then cut into 1 inch rounds</p><p>Slice your <strong>cucumber</strong> finely</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s] </strong>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654013722659-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654013722659-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654013722659-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654013722659-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1654013722659-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced cucumber</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and set aside until serving – this is your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654013724857-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654013724857-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654013724857-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654013724857-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1654013724857-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> pepper strips </strong>to one side of a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654013728074-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654013728074-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654013728074-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654013728074-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1654013728074-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Crack your <strong>egg[s]</strong> into a shallow bowl and beat lightly with a fork</p><p>Add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> [4 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> to a plate and season with<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>ground cumin</strong> with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> on a separate plate – these are your <strong>cumin breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654013740190-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654013740190-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654013740190-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654013740190-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1654013740190-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Coat the <strong>aubergine rounds</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add them to the <strong>beaten egg</strong> and finally press into the <strong>cumin</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> to evenly coat all over</p><p>Add the <strong>coated aubergine rounds</strong> to the other side of the baking tray[s] and then put in the oven for 20-25 min or until the aubergine is crisp, golden and cooked through – this is your <strong>crispy cumin aubergine & roasted pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654013743587-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654013743587-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654013743587-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654013743587-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1654013743587-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander & parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>When the aubergine and pepper are almost ready, add your <strong>naan[s]</strong> to a separate baking tray (or two!) and sprinkle with a little <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 3 min or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654013746617-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654013746617-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654013746617-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654013746617-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1654013746617-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, the <strong>pickling liquid</strong> from the sliced cucumber and 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>chilli sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1654013753490-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1654013753490-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1654013753490-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1654013753490-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1654013753490-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To serve, place a <strong>warmed naan</strong> on a plate and spread <strong>half</strong> your <strong>natural</strong> <strong>yoghurt </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chilli sauce</strong> over the top</p><p>Layer on the <strong>crispy cumin aubergine & roasted pepper </strong>with the <strong>quick-pickled cucumber </strong>and <strong>chopped herbs</strong>, then<strong> </strong>crumble over your <strong>feta</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>remaining yoghurt </strong>and <strong>chilli sauce</strong> all over and sprinkle with your <strong>crispy onions </strong>and enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
